# End-to-End RAG System Enhancement

This plan transforms the current prototype-level AgenticRag project into a fully functional, production-ready RAG configurator. The current backend uses InMemory document stores with largely mocked integrations; the frontend has UI scaffolding but missing configurations for most RAG types and no API key management. This plan covers all 10 feature areas the user requested.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a **very large** project touching ~15 files across backend and frontend. The plan is structured into 3 phases that should be implemented sequentially. Some features (like real Qdrant/Elasticsearch integration) require external service credentials—these will be optional with graceful fallbacks.

> [!WARNING]
> **Breaking changes**: The [DeployRequest](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/main.py#74-89) model in [main.py](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/main.py) will be extended with new fields (`apiKeys`, `privacyMode`, `explainability`). Existing deploy calls from the frontend will be updated to match. The deployment flow will also change to support hybrid deployment.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: Backend Foundation

---

#### [NEW] [vector_store_manager.py](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/services/vector_store_manager.py)

Central module for vector store creation and management:
- Factory function `create_document_store(config)` that returns the right store based on `dbType`, `cloudDb`, `localDb`
- **ChromaDB**: Real `chromadb.PersistentClient` integration with collection management
- **FAISS**: FAISS index creation with `faiss-cpu`, document serialization
- **Qdrant** (NEW cloud option): `qdrant-client` integration with API key support
- **Elasticsearch** (NEW cloud option): `elasticsearch` client integration
- **Hybrid mode**: Returns a tuple of (cloud_store, local_store) for dual retrieval
- **InMemory fallback**: Keeps current InMemory store as default

#### [NEW] [embedding_service.py](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/services/embedding_service.py)

Embedding model management:
- `get_embedder(model_id, api_key=None)` factory that returns Haystack-compatible embedders
- **Local BGE**: Uses `sentence-transformers` with `BAAI/bge-m3` model
- **OpenAI Ada**: Uses OpenAI embeddings API with user-provided key
- **Mistral** (NEW option): Mistral embeddings via API

#### [NEW] [llm_service.py](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/services/llm_service.py)

LLM provider management:
- `get_generator(model_id, api_key=None)` factory
- **Qwen local**: Current llama_cpp.server OpenAI-compatible endpoint
- **Mistral local** (NEW): Support for loading Mistral GGUF via llama_cpp
- **OpenAI GPT-4o**: Real OpenAI API integration with user key
- **Anthropic Claude**: Real Anthropic API integration with user key
- Key validation endpoint: `validate_api_key(provider, key)` 

#### [MODIFY] [scraper.py](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/services/scraper.py)

Enhance to support dynamic (JS-rendered) pages:
- Add `scrape_mode` parameter: `"static"` (current BeautifulSoup) or `"dynamic"` 
- Dynamic mode uses `playwright` (async) to render JS before extracting content
- Add `scrape_sitemap()` to crawl entire sites via sitemap.xml
- Better content extraction: prioritize `<article>`, `<main>`, structured data

#### [MODIFY] [document_parser.py](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/services/document_parser.py)

Expand document type support:
- Add **DOCX** parsing via `python-docx`
- Add **CSV** parsing with intelligent column extraction
- Add **HTML** file parsing (local HTML files)
- Add **Markdown** parsing
- Improve OCR: configure Tesseract path, add image preprocessing for better results

#### [MODIFY] [haystack_service.py](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/services/haystack_service.py)

Major rewrite to support real pipelines:
- Use `vector_store_manager` for real document stores instead of InMemory
- Use `embedding_service` for real embeddings
- Use `llm_service` for real LLM generators
- Implement **real DocumentSplitter** with configurable chunk size/overlap
- Implement proper pipeline building for each RAG type:
  - **Basic**: Standard retriever → prompt → LLM
  - **Conversational**: Add chat memory via Haystack's `ChatMessageWriter/Reader`
  - **Agentic**: Tool-calling with Haystack's `ToolInvoker` component  
  - **Graph RAG**: Knowledge graph construction with entity extraction
  - **Multimodal**: Multi-modal document handling
  - **Cross-lingual**: Translation component before/after retrieval
  - **Citation**: Source tracking in prompt template
  - **Real-time**: Streaming pipeline support
  - **Personalized**: User profile-based retrieval filtering
  - **Voice**: STT/TTS integration points
- Add **reranker** implementation using `TransformersSimilarityRanker`
- Add **explainability**: Return retrieval scores and source documents with answers
- **Privacy mode**: Strip PII from responses when enabled

#### [MODIFY] [rag_builder.py](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/services/rag_builder.py)

Expand deployment capabilities:
- **API deployment**: Generate FastAPI router with query endpoint (current behavior, enhanced)
- **Offline deployment**: Serialize pipeline to YAML + package dependencies list
- **Hybrid**: Both API + offline artifact
- Return comprehensive deployment metadata

#### [MODIFY] [agentic_logic.py](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/services/agentic_logic.py)

Implement real agentic capabilities:
- Define tool functions (web search, calculator, calendar lookup)
- Build agentic pipeline with tool routing
- Decision-making loop for multi-step reasoning

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/main.py)

Update API layer:
- Extend [DeployRequest](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/main.py#74-89) with: `apiKeys: dict`, `privacyMode: bool`, `explainability: bool`, `scrapeMode: str`
- Add `POST /api/validate-key` endpoint for API key validation
- Update `/api/visualize/{pipeline_id}` to return real pipeline graph data
- Add `POST /api/scrape` to accept `mode` param (static/dynamic)
- Enhanced error handling and logging

#### [MODIFY] [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Users/e629/Documents/AgenticRag/backend/requirements.txt)

Add new dependencies:
```
playwright
python-docx
faiss-cpu
qdrant-client
elasticsearch
anthropic
```

